Slooz - Food Ordering Backend ( Sorry, I got confused with the exact name,I wrote Slooz instead of slooze in whole codebase. I used ChatGPT for Coding Assistance) 
===============================

Hey there! This is the backend for Slooz, a food ordering system where different users have different powers (like superheroes, but for food delivery).

What's Cool About This?
------------------------

This system has three types of users, each with their own superpowers:

- Admins: The bosses who can do everything
- Managers: Regional persons who handle their country's operations (India or America)
- Members: Regular folks who can browse and order food

 here is that Managers and Members only see restaurants and orders from their own country. Admins? They see it all.

We're using GraphQL for the API (think of it as a smarter way to fetch data), JWT tokens for security (so nobody can pretend to be someone else), and PostgreSQL to store everything safely.

Who Can Do What?
----------------

Here's the breakdown of powers:

                                    Admin    Manager    Member
View restaurants & menu items       ✓         ✓         ✓
Create orders (add food)             ✓         ✓         ✓
Checkout & pay for orders            ✓         ✓         ✗
Cancel orders                        ✓         ✓         ✗
Add/modify payment methods           ✓         ✗         ✗


