What's Under the Hood?
----------------------

- Node.js - The engine that runs everything
- NestJS - framework that keeps our code organized
- GraphQL - A modern way to build APIs (better than REST
- Prisma - Makes talking to the database super easy
- PostgreSQL - Where we store all the data
- JWT - Security tokens so nobody can hack your account

What You Need Before Starting
------------------------------

Make sure you have these installed:
- Node.js (version 18 or newer)
- PostgreSQL (the database)
- npm (comes with Node.js)

Getting Started (The Easy Way)
-------------------------------

Step 1: Grab the code

First, download this project to your computer:

  git clone <your-repo-url>
  cd backend


Step 2: Install the dependencies

This downloads all the tools we need:

  npm install


Step 3: Set up your secrets

Copy the example file and add your database info:

  cp .env.example .env

Then open the .env file and update it with your details:

  DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/slooz?schema=public
  JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-here
  JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
  PORT=3000


Step 4: Create the database tables

This sets up all the tables we need:

  npx prisma migrate dev --name init


Step 5: Add some test data

This fills the database with our Marvel heroes and some restaurants:

  npx prisma db seed


Step 6: Fire it up!

Start the server:

  npm run start:dev


Step 7: Play around

Open your browser and go to:
  http://localhost:3000/graphql

You'll see a playground where you can test the API!

Try These Out (Example Queries)
--------------------------------

First, Log In

Let's log in as Nick Fury (the admin):

  mutation {
    login(input: { email: "nick@slooz.com", password: "password123" }) {
      token
      user {
        id
        name
        role
        country
      }
    }
  }

Copy the token you get back - you'll need it for everything else!


See What Restaurants Are Available

Add this to your HTTP headers:
  Authorization: Bearer <paste-your-token-here>

Then run:

  query {
    restaurants {
      id
      name
      country
      menuItems {
        id
        name
        price
      }
    }
  }


Order Some Food

Pick some items and create an order:

  mutation {
    createOrder(input: {
      items: [
        { menuItemId: "mi-taj-1", quantity: 2 },
        { menuItemId: "mi-taj-3", quantity: 1 }
      ]
    }) {
      id
      status
      totalAmount
      items {
        menuItem { name }
        quantity
        price
      }
    }
  }


Pay For Your Order (Managers & Admins Only)

  mutation {
    checkout(input: {
      orderId: "<order-id>",
      paymentMethodId: "pm-nick-1"
    }) {
      id
      status
      paymentMethodId
    }
  }


Changed Your Mind? Cancel It (Managers & Admins Only)

  mutation {
    cancelOrder(orderId: "<order-id>") {
      id
      status
    }
  }


Add a New Payment Method (Admins Only)

  mutation {
    createPaymentMethod(input: {
      type: "CREDIT_CARD",
      details: "Mastercard ending in 8888"
    }) {
      id
      type
      details
    }
  }

How Everything Is Organized
----------------------------

The code is split into folders:

src/
  auth/           - Login stuff, JWT tokens, security guards
  users/          - User accounts, roles, country assignments
  restaurants/    - Restaurant listings and menu items
  orders/         - Creating, canceling, and checking out orders
  cart/           - Shopping cart management
  payments/       - Payment methods (credit cards, etc.)
  prisma/         - Database connection helper
  common/         - Shared code used everywhere
  app.module.js   - The main app setup
  main.js         - Where everything starts

prisma/
  schema.prisma   - Database structure definition
  seed.js         - Test data 


Want to Run Tests?
------------------

Simple:

  npm run test


That's It!
